# Orchestrator — Run Foundation

## Slug
`trucking-freight-factoring-and-banking`
- Demo: `/demos/trucking-freight-factoring-and-banking/`
- Work-sample route: `/work-samples/trucking-freight-factoring-and-banking`
- Run dir: `upwork-runs/trucking-freight-factoring-and-banking/`

## What the client is hiring for
Senior TS/Node engineer to help migrate a mature freight-factoring + banking
(BaaS) platform for the trucking/logistics industry from PHP/Laravel+Flutter to a
modern **TypeScript monorepo**, inside an **AI-first (Claude Code) engineering
process**. Domains: factoring/receivables (FIDC), banking (BaaS), payments,
identity & RBAC. Brazilian fintech (PIX, BRT timezone) flavor. They value:
correctness with money (never floats for currency), real-DB integration tests,
skeptical review of AI-generated PRs.

## Non-negotiable constraints (from Michael's notes — honor exactly)
1. **Use their exact stack in the demo.** Backend must be **NestJS + Drizzle +
   Postgres** (TypeScript), frontend **Next.js 15 (App Router)**. This is the
   point of the proposal: prove fluency in the requested tools, not adjacent ones.
2. **Bridge the new Node backend to the existing Python backend.** mw-backend
   (Flask) cannot natively run NestJS. Plan a way to interface: the live demo
   should run a real NestJS+Drizzle service, with mw-backend (Flask) acting as a
   thin reverse-proxy / gateway in front so it deploys via the existing Surface
   auto-deploy watcher and same-origin model. **researcher + planner must resolve
   the concrete bridging mechanism** (e.g. Flask proxies `/api/factoring/*` to a
   locally-run Node process on the Surface, or Node service runs alongside and
   Flask forwards). Do NOT silently fall back to a Python reimplementation — the
   client specifically wants Node/NestJS/Drizzle.
3. **Money correctness:** integer minor units (cents/centavos) everywhere, never
   floats. Discriminated unions, strict TS, Zod validation on money paths. Make
   this visible in the demo (the client is "obsessive about correctness with
   money").
4. **Feature richness = 10/10.** Full, production-quality multi-feature app.

## Demo concept (direction for planner — refine, don't blindly accept)
A **freight-factoring + banking operations console** for a trucking fintech.
Candidate hero + supporting features (planner finalizes 1 hero + ≤2 supporting
per caps, but richness 10 means each is genuinely functional):
- **Invoice/receivable factoring flow (HERO):** carrier submits a freight invoice
  -> advance-rate + fee + reserve calc (integer cents) -> approval -> funded.
  FIDC ledger. This showcases money-correctness end to end.
- **Banking/BaaS ledger + PIX-style instant payout:** account balances, double-
  entry ledger, payout to driver. Brazilian rails nod.
- **Identity & RBAC:** roles (admin / underwriter / carrier / driver), real auth,
  permission-gated actions. Seed a demo login and record creds.
- **AI-factory / spec panel (optional flavor):** surfaces the "humans architect,
  AI builds, humans verify" workflow the client runs — ties demo to the pitch.

Real integration-test angle: include a small Postgres-backed test suite (no mocks
on money paths) and mention green CI — directly answers their must-have.

## Backend decision (greenlit — needs a blueprint AND a Node service)
This run SHOULD use a backend (auth, ledger, real DB). Two-tier:
- Real **NestJS + Drizzle + Postgres** service = the substance.
- **mw-backend Flask blueprint** = gateway/proxy so it deploys + serves same-origin
  per CLAUDE.md. Keep it thin; do not touch auth/DB schema of mw-backend.
- Seed a demo account; record credentials in the run dir for deploy-test login.
deploy-test will exercise the LIVE flow incl. login + a factoring funding run.

## Proposal "To apply" answers (proposal-writer must include verbatim-in-spirit)
The posting asks three questions. Michael's substance:
1. **Non-trivial AI-shipped feature:** the **Cornerstone Construction** demo (a
   prior work-sample). The Claude-Code agentic workflow built a full frontend
   from design -> develop -> test. Show **screenshots of Michael's Claude Workflow
   Studio set to the `with-ceo` layout** — the most recent desktop screenshot is
   `~/Desktop/Screenshot 2026-06-16 at 10.42.18 AM.png` (use this). What Michael
   had to correct: (a) a navbar link visibility issue, (b) project images
   duplicated per-category instead of unique per project, (c) a navigation quirk —
   clicking a project on the homepage opened the projects page but not the modal
   for that specific project; he rewired it to open the correct project modal.
   Explain the agentic workflow + how he verified.
2. **TS/Node codebase proud of:** *this* demo (the NestJS+Drizzle factoring app).
   Reinforces why coding the demo in their exact stack matters — it IS the answer.
3. **One thing teams get wrong about AI-assisted dev:** they fear AI gets too much
   wrong / isn't a capable partner. With strong prompting, good workflows, and a
   skilled engineer checking and guiding outputs, AI-assisted dev is extremely
   powerful and ships production-ready features.

## Design guidance (bespoke — NOT michaelwegter.com's look)
Brazilian fintech / logistics-banking aesthetic. Trust + money + motion. Think
clean neobank dashboard (Nubank/cluster of BaaS dashboards) crossed with freight
ops: deep ink/navy or near-black base, a confident fintech accent (consider a
green or violet — researcher to check client/competitor palettes and PIX
conventions), crisp data-dense tables, monospaced numerals for money, tabular
figures. Real font families (e.g. Inter/Geist for UI, a mono for ledgers).
planner defines exact palette+type. Deck + one-pager echo the demo's language.

## Pipeline + layout
Recommended graph (backend + live deploy matter):
intake -> planner -> ceo -> researcher -> demo-builder -> deploy -> deploy-test ->
media-capture -> proposal-writer -> evaluator.
Load **`with-ceo`** + **`with-deploy`** studio layouts. CEO pairs after planner
and after demo-builder (richness 10, money-correctness, and the Python<->Node
bridge are the things most worth a supervisor pass).

## Quality gates to enforce downstream
- Exact stack used (NestJS+Drizzle+Postgres / Next.js 15). No substituting Python
  logic for the Node service the client asked about.
- Integer-cents money math; no floats on money paths; Zod-validated.
- Real auth + seeded demo login recorded; live route returns 200 post-deploy.
- Demo link in BOTH cover letter and deck; three "To apply" answers present.
- No em/en dashes anywhere; Michael's voice; bespoke fintech design.
- eval-report.md passes all hard gates.

